LOVE doctor, Musa Sukwene, has Mzansi eating out of the palm of his hand!That&rsquo;s because this crooner has achieved what others like him have failed to pull off . . . He has made soul ballads great again!Through his heart-warming music, this hard-act-to-follow musician has reminded Mzansi about the innocent charm of falling in love.So, it should come as no surprise that his love vibes have earned him two nominations in the upcoming Metro FM Awards.And Musa will certainly aim to turn his African pop and song of the Year proposals into accolades on awards night at the Inkosi Albert Luthuli International Convention Centre in Durban, KwaZulu-Natal, on 25 February.Asked what this meant to him, Musa said he was over the moon that his hit single, Mthande, had got the nod.&ldquo;I&rsquo;m so happy about the nominations and, especially, recognition from my supporters,&rdquo; Musa said.He was chuffed that the song he had worked on with his mentor and award-winning producer, Robbie Malinga, had found a home in the hearts of South Africans.&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve always worked hard, and the fruits of my labour are finally ripening,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;On my Mr Serious album, I bared my heart and soul to the country!&rdquo;Musa told Sunday Sun he appreciated the wave of success he was enjoying, but stressed that he wanted to keep the momentum going.&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve already started work on my next project.&rdquo; To vote for Musa to win: Dial *120*1512# and follow instructions.